# cppcheck suppression list for QKeyboard.
# One suppression per line: <id>[:<file-glob>]. See:
# https://cppcheck.sourceforge.io/manual.pdf ("Suppressions")
# Keep this list to genuine false positives, not real findings papered over —
# per CLAUDE.md's engineering-discipline rules, a suppression that's no
# longer needed should be removed, not left "just in case".

# cppcheck is run without a real Qt install on the PATH it can resolve
# headers from (CI installs Qt for the build matrix, not the lint job), so
# every Qt header include is unresolvable. This is expected and not a real
# finding — cppcheck still analyzes the translation unit's own code using
# the -I include/ path we do provide.
missingIncludeSystem

# This is a library: most public API in include/qkeyboard/*.h is
# called by consumers (examples/, tests/, or external users) outside what
# a single-repo cppcheck run can see, and Qt's moc/signal-slot machinery
# calls slots/signals that never appear as a direct call in source either.
unusedFunction

# Q_OBJECT/moc-generated code and Qt's signal/slot macros aren't visible to
# cppcheck (moc output isn't part of the source tree it scans), which
# produces noise around QObject-derived classes' constructors/signals that
# don't apply to plain C++ code.
unmatchedSuppression

# Same root cause as missingIncludeSystem above (no real Qt install on
# cppcheck's path): without Qt's headers, cppcheck can't expand Qt macros
# like Q_PROPERTY, Q_OBJECT, signals:, and slots:, and reports each as an
# "unknown macro" error.
unknownMacro

# tst_translations.cpp's i18nFilePath() uses adjacent-string-literal
# concatenation with the build-injected QKW_I18N_DIR macro
# (QStringLiteral(QKW_I18N_DIR "/qkeyboard_%1.ts")) - a normal,
# valid C++ pattern (same as __FILE__ ": message"), but cppcheck's
# QKW_I18N_DIR-defined configuration variant substitutes a placeholder
# value it can't actually concatenate with the adjacent string literal,
# producing a false "syntax error" purely from cppcheck's own macro
# substitution, not a real problem in the source.
syntaxError:tests/tst_translations.cpp
